## ⛔ Prime directive (G ruling 1d — halt-and-report)

This is a **conditional patch**. The re-pin is **dependency / API-compatibility work only**. It must
preserve:
- the **public canister API** — Candid interface unchanged;
- the **receipt schema** — CVDR field set + encoding;
- the **hash formulas** — every preimage / domain-separated hash input;
- the **8-slot stable-memory layout** — MemoryIds 100–107, incl. base+5 `finalization_lock`, base+6
  receipt store, base+7 `tombstoned_at` — *including the serialized encoding of each stable structure's
  contents*.

If any adaptation needed to compile under ic-cdk 0.18 / is-0.7 would change **any** of the above,
**STOP and report**. It is then no longer a v0.4.1 patch and routes to a broader gate / new version line.
Do **not** silently absorb such a change to make it build.

